usdSlepMIBS.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdSlepMIBS.description: The Serial Line Encapulation Protocol (SLEP) MIB for the Unisphere Networks Inc. enterprise.

usdSlepNextIfIndex.name: usdSlepNextIfIndex
usdSlepNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdSlepIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdSlepIfTable.name: usdSlepIfTable
usdSlepIfTable.description: The parameters for the SLEP service on this interface.

usdSlepIfEntry.name: usdSlepIfEntry
usdSlepIfEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular SLEP interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable

usdSlepIfIndex.name: usdSlepIfIndex
usdSlepIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEntry.

usdSlepKeepAliveTimer.name: usdSlepKeepAliveTimer
usdSlepKeepAliveTimer.description: The interface keep alive timer for this entry. The time in seconds that this entity will wait for sending a keep-alive-message to the remote SLEP entity, and the time in seconds that this entity will wait for the reception of a keep-alive-message from the remote SLEP entity.

usdSlepIfLowerIfIndex.name: usdSlepIfLowerIfIndex
usdSlepIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this SLEP interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdSlepIfRowStatus.name: usdSlepIfRowStatus
usdSlepIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdSlepIfRowStatus usdSlepIfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdSlepIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdSlepNextIfIndex. The interface identified by usdSlepIfLowerIfIndex must exist, and must be an interface type that permits layering of SLEP Interface above it. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdSlepDownWhenLooped.name: usdSlepDownWhenLooped
usdSlepDownWhenLooped.description: The down-when-looped control for this entry. This attribute determines if loop detection is enabled for the interface. If set to disable, loop detection is disabled for the interface.

usdSlepIfStatisticsTable.name: usdSlepIfStatisticsTable
usdSlepIfStatisticsTable.description: The statistics for the SLEP service on this interface.

usdSlepIfStatisticsEntry.name: usdSlepIfStatisticsEntry
usdSlepIfStatisticsEntry.description: The statistics for a particular SLEP interface.

usdSlepIfStatsIndex.name: usdSlepIfStatsIndex
usdSlepIfStatsIndex.description: The ifIndex value of that identifies this entry.

usdSlepKeepAliveFailures.name: usdSlepKeepAliveFailures
usdSlepKeepAliveFailures.description: The number of link drops due to keep-alive failures.

usdSlepLinkStatusTooLongPackets.name: usdSlepLinkStatusTooLongPackets
usdSlepLinkStatusTooLongPackets.description: The number of packets that were too long for this SLEP entity.

usdSlepLinkStatusBadFCSs.name: usdSlepLinkStatusBadFCSs
usdSlepLinkStatusBadFCSs.description: The number of FCS's errors for this SLEP entity.

usdSlepCompliance.name: usdSlepCompliance
usdSlepCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere SLEP MIB. This compliance statement became obsolete when the usdSlepDownWhenLooped object was added.

usdSlepCompliance2.name: usdSlepCompliance2
usdSlepCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere SLEP MIB.

usdSlepGroup.name: usdSlepGroup
usdSlepGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of SLEP interfaces in a Unisphere product. This group became obsolete when the usdSlepDownWhenLooped object was added.

usdSlepGroup2.name: usdSlepGroup2
usdSlepGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of SLEP interfaces in a Unisphere product.
